cJ0N5yStBk9CjXA","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5IDNKg5CMSstGl","target":"rec5g1fzEKYzCO1Re","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5IDNKg5CMSstGl","target":"reczmi6XtMXALtcNn","label":"event"},{"source":"rec5IDNKg5CMSstGl","target":"reciunQ6bRGaY2gib","label":"event"},{"source":"rec5IDNKg5CMSstGl","target":"recW2cNLqUyMIV6O7","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recIyyaWNj5SNJ80m","ref":"2Kgs.24.1","text":"In his days Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up, and Jehoiakim became his servant three years: then he turned and rebelled against him."},{"id":"recU0db8FVaZ31NtM","ref":"2Kgs.24.2","text":"And the LORD sent against him bands of the Chaldees, and bands of the Syrians, and bands of the Moabites, and bands of the children of Ammon, and sent them against Judah to destroy it, according to the word of the LORD, which he spake by his servants the prophets."},{"id":"recw8NyUmrTLGDDa1","ref":"2Kgs.24.3","text":"Surely at the commandment of the LORD came this upon Judah, to remove them out of his sight, for the sins of Manasseh, according to all that he did;"},{"id":"rec679TkUTdYfZMzu","ref":"2Kgs.24.4","text":"And also for the innocent blood that he shed: for he filled Jerusalem with innocent blood; which the LORD would not pardon."},{"id":"recwIALvqzJ3WtIvc","ref":"2Kgs.24.5","text":"Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?"},{"id":"rec4GsbcQVrUN0aQS","ref":"2Kgs.24.6","text":"So Jehoiakim slept with his fathers: and Jehoiachin his son reigned in his stead.","year":-599},{"id":"recp6sKtpDsD4Ty8v","ref":"2Kgs.24.7","text":"And the king of Egypt came not again any more out of his land: for the king of Babylon had taken from the river of Egypt unto the river Euphrates all that pertained to the king of Egypt.","year":-599},{"id":"recK1HqhgW5fdTU7w","ref":"2Kgs.24.8","text":"Jehoiachin was eighteen years old when he began to reign, and he reigned in Jerusalem three months. And his mother’s name was Nehushta, the daughter of Elnathan of Jerusalem.","year":-599}]}
